The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Musharraf chief guest for final
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Musharraf chief guest for final
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	Karachi: Pakistans cricket-loving President, Pervez Musharraf, will be the chief guest during Sundays Asia Cup final. Hes also the patron-in-chief of the hosts, the Pakistan Cricket Board.         
	According to The Telegraphs sources, theres a good chance that the Sri Lankan President, Mahinda Rajapaksa, could also turn up as his country has made the title-round.         
	Confirmation should come within 48 hours, one of the sources pointed out.                                                                                                                          
